OL,3,C'Questions left unanswered' at South
OL,4,CWest Water meeting, residents say
OL,6,FOne man who attended the meeting said
OL,7,Fwhile he recognised Ms Davy's apology,
OL,8,Fhe felt she didn't gage the strength
OL,9,Fof feeling from local people about the
OL,10,Fimpact of the incident.
OL,12,F"Ms Davy's main job there tonight was
OL,13,Fto apologise unreservedly. What she
OL,14,Fdidn't do is understand the actual
OL,15,Ffeeling of the anger and the distrust
OL,16,Ftowards South West Water," he said.
OL,18,FAnother resident who attended the
OL,19,Fmeeting said she felt "lots of
OL,20,Fquestions were left unanswered."
